      <h1 class='title'>Pensions: supplementary</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c278GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_278gc' title='Col. 278GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c278GC' name='column_278gc' href='#column_278gc' rel='bookmark'>278GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03665'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_276' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        22 If&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) a Part 1 order made by virtue of paragraph 20 or 21 imposes any requirement on the person responsible for a pension arrangement ("the first arrangement"),</li>
        <li>(b) the civil partner with pension rights acquires rights under another pension arrangement ("the new arrangement") which are derived (directly or indirectly) from the whole of that civil partner's rights under the first arrangement, and</li>
        <li>(c) the person responsible for the new arrangement has been given notice in accordance with regulations made by the Lord Chancellor, the Part 1 order has effect as if it had been made instead in respect of the person responsible for the new arrangement.</li></ol>
      </p>
      <ol class='xoxo'>
        
